It was a night of glitz, glamour and sizzling performances by the likes of Babes Wodumo, Kelly Khumalo, Kwesta and Khuli Chana.Kwesta was the big winner and walked away with six awards, while Amanda Black got three awards.The red carpet was crawling with the who's who of the entertainment world, all dressed to the nines. Here s our pick of the best and worst dressed of the night.Bonang stole the show in a gorgeous crimson red gown by Orapeleng Modutle.A post shared by Bonang Matheba (@bonang_m) on May 27, 2017 at 8:14am PDT Red was clearly a trend for the night with Moozlie wearing a stunning red gown by Gert Johan Coetzee.A post shared by Moozlie (@moozlie) on May 27, 2017 at 11:19am PDT Pearl rocked the 'naked' dress trend in this sheer body-hugging dress from Cinnel Store.A post shared by Pearl Thusi (@pearlthusi) on May 28, 2017 at 12:17am PDT Kelly KhumaloKelly looked like a princess in this voluminous orange gown by Tsotetsi KL.A post shared by Kelly Khumalo (@kellykhumaloza) on May 27, 2017 at 12:11pm PDT Thando's gold exposed-shoulder gown didn t quite hit the mark.A post shared by Thando Thabethe (@thando_thabethe) on May 27, 2017 at 12:47pm PDT Khanyi's embellished sheer dress revealed too much skin. So much so, some labelled it 'inappropriate' for prime-time viewing.A post shared by Khanyi Mbau METANOIA (@mbaureloaded) on May 29, 2017 at 12:01am PDT additional reporting Karishma Thakurdin.